3 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision in KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
4 Secretary of State shall cause the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this Act and the
5 entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in Section
6 2 of this Act to be published at least one time in a newspaper of general circulation
7 published in this state, and shall also cause to be published at the same time and in the
8 same manner the fact that the amendment will be submitted to the voters for their
9 acceptance or rejection at the next regular election at which members of the General
10 Assembly are to be voted for. The publication required by this section and KRS 118.415
11 shall be made no later than the first Tuesday in August preceding the election at which
12 the amendment is to be voted on.
13 Section 5. Notwithstanding any provision in KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
14 Secretary of State, not later than the second Monday after the second Tuesday in August
15 preceding the next regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be
16 chosen in a year in which there is not an election for President and Vice President of the
17 United States, or not later than the Thursday after the first Tuesday in September
18 preceding a regular election in a year in which there is an election for President and Vice
19 President of the United States, shall certify the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this
20 Act and the entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky
21 contained in Section 2 of this Act to the county clerk of each county, and the county clerk
22 shall have the entirety of the amendment and the question, as so certified, indicated on
23 the ballots provided to the voters in paper or electronic form as applicable to the voting
24 machines in use in each county or precinct.
